InclusionCriteria: All children, young people and adults who fit the selection criteria from across all the practices can be referred to the allergy clinic.
InclusionCriteria_NoSW: children young people adults fit selection criteria practices referred allergy clinic

InclusionCriteria: All patients and parents / carers where appropriate must be deemed capable of giving informed consent to take part in the research project.
InclusionCriteria_NoSW: patients parents carers appropriate deemed capable giving informed consent research project

InclusionCriteria: Infants under two with suspected food allergy
Infants under two with moderate-to-severe eczema not responding to standard treatment.
InclusionCriteria_NoSW: Infants moderate-to-severe eczema responding standard treatment

InclusionCriteria: Children and young people (up to 16 years of age) with suspected allergic rhinitis symptoms that are unresponsive to a combination of oral antihistamines and nasal steroids
InclusionCriteria_NoSW: Children young people 16 years age suspected allergic rhinitis symptoms unresponsive combination oral antihistamines nasal steroids

InclusionCriteria: Young people and adults (from 16 years of age) with a history of anaphylaxis or suspected anaphylaxis
InclusionCriteria_NoSW: Young people adults 16 years age history anaphylaxis suspected anaphylaxis
